# Docker & Infrastructure Conventions

## Docker Compose Services (target state)
- `postgres` — PostgreSQL 16 with RLS init scripts
- `kafka` — KRaft mode (no ZooKeeper), with kafka-ui on :8090
- `elasticsearch` — Single-node ES 8 for dev
- `redis` — Redis 7
- `neo4j` — Neo4j 5
- `minio` — S3-compatible object storage
- `dashboard` — Next.js app (port 3000)
- `go_service` — Go service (port 8080)
- `fastapi_service` — FastAPI service (port 8000)

## Dockerfile Best Practices
- Multi-stage builds (build stage + minimal runtime)
- Non-root user in runtime stage
- HEALTHCHECK instruction in every Dockerfile
- Pin base image versions (e.g., `node:24-alpine`, `golang:1.25-alpine`, `python:3.11-slim`)
- Copy dependency files first, install deps, then copy source (layer caching)

## Environment Variables
- All config via env vars (12-factor). Never hardcode secrets.
- Use `.env.example` (committed) as template. `.env` is gitignored.
